Do not exceed 3 clarification questions.

6.  STEP-BY-STEP EXECUTION PLAN

Step 1: Initiate Local Brain and launch Geo-Grid configuration workflow.

Step 2: Select 5 primary keywords aligned to highest commercial intent.

Step 3: Configure grid settings: - Radius: 5 miles - Configuration:
Circle - Grid density: Default competitive density level - Pin layers: 5
keyword layers

Step 4: Set scan timing: - Start Time: 9:00 AM (local time) - Refresh
Interval: Weekly

Step 5: Deploy tracking.

Step 6: Validate first scan completion.

Step 7: Document configuration settings.

7.  APPROVAL GATE(S)

Before deployment:

Present: - Selected keywords - Grid radius + configuration - Scan
frequency - Start time

Obtain approval before activating weekly automation.

8.  DELIVERABLES / OUTPUTS

-   Geo-Grid Configuration Summary
-   Confirmed 5 tracked keywords
-   Screenshot or confirmation of grid deployment
-   Weekly tracking schedule confirmation
-   Baseline ranking summary (first scan snapshot)
-   Documentation of configuration settings

9.  VERIFICATION / SUCCESS CRITERIA

After execution, verify:

-   5 keywords are actively tracking
-   Grid is set to 5-mile circle
-   Scan time is 9:00 AM local
-   Refresh interval is weekly
-   All five keyword layers are visible
-   First scan data successfully populates

User confirms configuration is correct.

10. EDGE CASES / STOP CONDITIONS

STOP if:

-   Keywords are too broad (e.g., single-word category terms)
-   Geo radius conflicts with business service model
-   SAB address conflicts with grid center
-   No GBP is connected
-   Weekly automation fails to schedule

Do NOT proceed without: - Project confirmation - Keyword confirmation -
User approval
